    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nNo way to restart without fully closing and starting with the same command.\r\n\r\nSee also vim/vim#13904. Decided to open a separate issue here as it seems that implementation will be different and the Vim issue got stale.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nAvailable either a `:restart` command or `vim.api.nvim_restart()` function which can restart an instance without \"close-reopen\" loop.\r\n\r\nThe effect is expected to be at least the same as (in layman language):\r\n- Do Neovim closing process as normal *but* stop just before actually terminating the process.\r\n- Execute startup sequence as if a new process has started. This can also result in preserving \"startup related\" data like argument list, CLI options, etc. Maybe even tabpages/windows/buffers for better interactive experience.\r\n\r\nI see this feature as useful in at least for following use cases:\r\n- Clean reloading of user config after there were some changes made.\r\n- Restarting instance through RPC without dealing with \"close and drop connection -> reopen with proper arguments -> reconnect\".",
