            "body": "Indeed, missed that.\r\n\r\nHowever:\r\n- Since that issue was closed, there were rewrites of how Neovim startup process works. I specifically thought that after Neovim has TUI run in a separate process, this might be not that complicated to implement. Cost-benefit analysis might have shifted here. Hence the \"needs:discussion\" label.\r\n- The benefit of available restart through RPC seems to be a valid argument for having it in core.\r\n- Suggestion to move this functionality to plugin (which are mostly meant to work *inside* current session) to me seems a bit far-fetched.",
